Defendant Nicole L Fandry in court with attorney John Alexander Cabranes.  Joanne L. Hardtke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing proceeds.  Statements made by the state, defense counsel and defendant.

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, & 3 (AMENDED TO MISDEMEANORS):   Defendant sentenced to serve 6 months at the HOUSE OF CORRECTION, consecutive to each other. 
Credit for ZERO days time served. 

COURT STAYS sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for a period of 2 years under the supervision of Wisconsin Department of Corrections.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, & 3 - CONCURRENT TO EACH OTHER): 
* Comply with the standard rules of probation.
* No contact with the victims, Expert Roofing Inc. and its employees.
* No contact with the co-actor/brother-in-law.
* PAY DNA surcharge - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* PAY the balance of all applicable court costs, fees, and surcharges - to be paid over a period of probation.  Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
* Obtain employment.
* Enroll in school.
* PAY restitution in the amount of $15,351.41 payable to Expert Roofing Inc.
  
Appeal rights given.

Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
